M.SER v1.0 - README [Monitor. system events and resources]


Description :
M.SER is an linux application that can combine logs to a human readable mode and stores that in a dynamic html page. The name of this application stands for monitor system events and resources, it can collect authentication logs, online users, ram and cpu usages and bw usages.

Dependencies :
uptime
whoami
sed
cat
head
tail
cut
awk
date
grep
mv
cp
rm
iostat
free
ifconfig
netstat
users
wc
rev


Check dependencies :
sudo chmod +x install.sh
sudo ./install.sh -c


Install iostat on debian systems :
sudo apt-get install sysstat


Install iostat on redhat systems :
sudo yum install sysstat


Install :
sudo chmod +x install.sh
sudo ./install.sh -i


Usage :
After install, just open http://example.com/


Uninstall :
sudo rm -r /opt/M.SER_v1.0/
sudo rm -f /YOUR-WEB-SERVER-ADDRESS/css/bootstrap.min.css
sudo rm -f /YOUR-WEB-SERVER-ADDRESS/css/heroic-features.css
sudo rm -f /YOUR-WEB-SERVER-ADDRESS/index.html


Tested on :
CentOS 7.2.1511 minimal - 64 Bit
CentOS 6.6 minimal - 64 Bit
CentOS 6.3 minimal - 32 Bit
Debian 8.1.0 netinstall - 64 Bit
Debian 8.4.0 netinstall - 64 Bit
Debian 6.0.6 netinstall - 32 Bit
Debian 7.8.0 netinstall - 64 Bit


Notes :
You should run program as root.
SELinux maybe prevention index.html for changes.
